# Bonsai is a bash plugin. A CRLF anywhere in a shell script — especially in the
# shebang — breaks bash on every platform ("bad interpreter", "$'\r': command
# not found"), and a `[[ "$x" == "$y" ]]` compare silently fails when one side
# carries a stray \r. On Windows, Git's default `core.autocrlf=true` would
# rewrite these files to CRLF on checkout, so the plugin would die the moment a
# hook fired. Pin every text file to LF so a Windows checkout is byte-identical
# to a macOS/Linux one.
* text=auto eol=lf

# Be explicit for the executable + data files that must never gain a CR.
*.sh    text eol=lf
*.bash  text eol=lf
*.bats  text eol=lf
*.json  text eol=lf
*.md    text eol=lf
*.yml   text eol=lf
*.yaml  text eol=lf
*.svg   text eol=lf

# Binary assets — never normalize line endings.
*.png   binary
*.jpg   binary
*.gif   binary
*.ico   binary
